{
  "id": "7ef846a6e4d3918e",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/skelar/b1f23ef8-1709-423b-aafa-463c0b8368ce/application",
    "company": "skelar",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "7ef846a6e4d3918e",
    "department": "Finance",
    "description": "[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/3a2721ac-0cf6-4bb5-a785-483b8d1018c3/Ashby_header.png]\n\nSKELAR is a venture builder that creates international tech businesses according to the guidelines of venture capital investment.\n\nWe are looking for a structured and detail-oriented International Accountant to join our International Reporting and Tax Compliance team. In this role, you will take ownership of VAT reporting processes for Cyprus companies and help build and scale our international accounting function.\n\nThis position is ideal for someone who enjoys working with financial data, building clear processes, and improving them through automation and technology. If you are someone who loves structured systems, notices every discrepancy in a dataset, and enjoys turning complex information into clear insights — this role is for you.\n\nYou will work with multiple international entities and support VAT compliance across our growing portfolio of global tech businesses.\n\nWhat you will do:\n\n - Coordinate the collection and organization of invoices and supporting documentation required for VAT reporting across Cyprus entities.\n\n - Process financial documents using AI tools to extract and structure financial data.\n\n - Prepare and review VAT reports, validating the completeness and accuracy of financial information.\n\n - Communicate and coordinate with external tax consultants in Cyprus, providing reporting packages and supporting documentation.\n\n - Review and approve VAT returns prepared by external advisors, ensuring compliance and accuracy before submission.\n\n - Lead the VAT refund process in Cyprus, coordinating documentation and managing communication with advisors and stakeholders.\n\n - Prepare VAT-related analytics and insights to support internal decision-making and financial planning.\n\n - Participate in building and developing the international accounting function within SKELAR.\n\n - Identify opportunities to automate and improve VAT reporting processes, implementing solutions that increase efficiency and data quality.\n\nSkills and experience needed to join the board:\n\n - 1–3 years of experience in accounting, finance, or tax (Big 4, consulting firms, or international businesses will be a plus).\n\n - Strong understanding of accounting fundamentals and document workflows.\n\n - Exceptional attention to detail and ability to maintain high data accuracy.\n\n - Structured thinking and strong organizational skills.\n\n - Analytical mindset and ability to work with financial data.\n\n - Interest in process optimization and automation.\n\n - Strong Excel / Google Sheets skills.\n\n - Upper-intermediate English (both written and spoken).\n\n - Proactive mindset and willingness to take ownership of processes.\n\nWe are especially excited to meet someone who:\n\n - loves structure, clarity, and well-organized financial processes\n\n - has a natural perfectionist mindset and high standards for accuracy\n\n - enjoys improving systems and building smarter ways of working\n\n - takes pride in creating processes that scale with the business\n\nSKELAR is a place for self-realization of talents who are able to create successful companies. We call such companies the next big everything. We believe in their power and scale.\n\nIn addition to our businesses, we have the SKELAR Foundation — a charitable foundation created by company employees. As part of the initiative, we create and finance projects that contribute to overcoming the consequences of the war and the reconstruction of Ukraine.\n\nWe will keep developing tech businesses, conquering global markets, and working for the victory of Ukraine 🇺🇦\n\nWhat we offer:\n\n - Competitive salary;\n\n - Significant impact on a rapidly growing business and contribution to how it shapes up;\n\n - Ample career opportunities for ambitious growth and development;\n\n - Working alongside professionals from top local and international companies (Big Law, Big 4, McKinsey, Horizon, Bolt, Didi, etc.);\n\n - Flat organizational structure without hierarchical barriers;\n\n - Access to internal and external courses, seminars, and a corporate library;\n\n - Comfortable working environment with all necessary equipment and complimentary breakfasts, lunches, and snacks in the office;\n\n - 20 days of paid vacation, medical insurance, and various sports activities for employees.\n\nLet's build the next big everything together.\n\n[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/bf8afb62-59f5-436b-b500-74f06bd0bb6e/Ashby_footer_eng.png]",
